  "text": "Divide-and-conquer is a widely-adopted problemsolving philosophy which has been demonstrated to be successful in many computer vision tasks, e.g. object detection and tracking [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Instead of solving a complete and huge problem, divide-and-conquer suggests decomposing the problem into several sub-problems and solving them in different constrained contexts. Figure 1 illustrates this idea with a binary classification problem. Finding a decision boundary in the original problem space is difficult and leads to a sophisticated nonlinear model, but linear decision models could be more easily obtained when solving the subproblems.",
